{"title_page": "Toba Samosir Regency", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->| name                            = Toba Regency\n| native_name                     = Kabupaten Toba\n| other_name                      = \n| native_name_lang                = id<!-- Indonesian -->sumut\n| image_skyline                   = \n| image_alt                       = \n| image_caption                   = \n| type                            = [[List of regencies and cities of Indonesia|Regency]]\n| image_seal                      = Lambang Kabupaten Toba Samosir.jpeg\n| seal_alt                        = Toba Regency Logo\n| motto                           = \"Tampakna do Rantosna, Rimni Tahi do Gogona\"\n| image_map                       = Lokasi Sumatra Utara Kabupaten Toba Samosir.svg\n| map_alt                         = \n| map_caption                     = \n| coordinates                     = \n| coordinates_footnotes           = \n| subdivision_type                = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n| subdivision_name                = {{IDN}}\n| subdivision_type1               = [[Provinces of Indonesia|Province]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[North Sumatra]]\n| seat_type                       = [[Regency seat]]\n| seat                            = [[Balige]]\n| leader_title                    = Regent\n| leader_name                     = Darwin Siagian\n| leader_title1                   = Vice Regent\n| leader_name1                    = Hulman Sitorus\n| leader_title2                   = Chairman of Council of Representatives\n| leader_name2                    = Effendi S. Panangian Napitupulu ([[Golkar]])\n| leader_title3                   = Vice Chairmen of Council of Representatives\n| leader_name3                    = Candrow Manurung ([[Nasdem]]) and Mangatas Silaen ([[PDI-P]])\n| area_footnotes                  = \n| area_total_km2                  = 2328.8\n| elevation_min_m                 = \n| elevation_max_m                 = \n| elevation_m                     = \n| population_as_of                = 2015\n| population_total                = 179600\n| population_density_km2          = auto\n| population_footnotes            = \n| timezone1                       = [[Time in Indonesia|WIB]]\n| utc_offset1                     = +7\n| website                         = {{URL|http://www.tobasamosirkab.go.id/}}\n| footnotes                       = \n| official_name                   = Kabupaten Toba\n}}\n\n'''Toba Regency''' a landlocked [[Regencies of Indonesia|regency]] in [[North Sumatra]]. Its seat is [[Balige]]. The regency covers an area of 2,328.8 square kilometres and according to the 2010 census it had a population of 172,933; the 2015 Census showed the population having risen to 179,600.<ref>Badan Pusat Statistik, Jakarta, 2016.</ref> It includes the eastern shore of the vast inland [[Lake Toba]].\n\n== Administration ==\nThe regency is divided administratively into sixteen [[Districts of Indonesia|districts]] (''kecamatan''), tabulated below with their 2010 Census populations:<ref name=\"Biro Pusat Statistik 2011\">Biro Pusat Statistik, Jakarta, 2011.</ref>\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n|-\n! Name  || Population<br>Census 2010\n|-\n| [[Balige]] ||align=\"right\"|36,653\n|-\n| [[Tampahan]] ||align=\"right\"|4,290\n|-\n| [[Lagu Boti]] ||align=\"right\"|18,359\n|-\n| [[Habinsaran]] ||align=\"right\"|15,453\n|-\n| [[Borbor]] ||align=\"right\"|6,790\n|-\n| [[Nassau (district)|Nassau]] ||align=\"right\"|7,219\n|-\n| [[Silaen]] ||align=\"right\"|12,105\n|-\n| [[Sigumpar]] ||align=\"right\"|7,404\n|-\n| [[Porsea]] ||align=\"right\"|12,810\n|-\n| [[Pintu Pohan Meranti]] ||align=\"right\"|7,070\n|-\n| [[Siantar Narumonda]] ||align=\"right\"|5,714\n|-\n| [[Parmaksian]] ||align=\"right\"|10,275\n|-\n| [[Lumban Julu]] ||align=\"right\"|8,150\n|-\n| [[Uluan]] ||align=\"right\"|6,983\n|-\n| [[Ajibata]] ||align=\"right\"|7,221\n|-\n| [[Bonatua Lunasi]] ||align=\"right\"|6,632\n|}\n\n==Orchid Paradise==\nTwo scientists explored the Eden Park tourist forest in Sionggang village in Toba Regency for four years and have successfully identified almost 200 new species of forest orchids. The area is an orchid paradise, in which thousands of other orchid species can be found.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2011/10/24/scene-toba-orchid-paradise-yields-200-new-species.html |title=Scene: Toba \u2018orchid paradise\u2019 yields 200 new species |date=October 24, 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Sigura-Gura waterfall==\nSigura-gura waterfall, which is the highest waterfall in Indonesia at {{convert|250|m|ft}} tall, is located {{convert|250|km|mi}} from [[Medan]] or a 2 to 3 hour long drive. Below the waterfall, one can do [[White water]] rafting.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gudangwisata.com/air-terjun-sigura-gura.html |title=Air Terjun Sigura-Gura |date=March 27, 2013|language=id}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{commons|Category:Toba Samosir Regency|Toba Samosir Regency}}\n{{North Sumatra}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{coord|2.3979|N|99.2168|E|source:wikidata|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Regencies of North Sumatra]]\n\n{{NSumatra-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->| name                            = Toba Regency\n| native_name                     = Kabupaten Toba\n| other_name                      = \n| native_name_lang                = id<!-- Indonesian -->sumut\n| image_skyline                   = \n| image_alt                       = \n| image_caption                   = \n| type                            = [[List of regencies and cities of Indonesia|Regency]]\n| image_seal                      = Lambang Kabupaten Toba Samosir.jpeg\n| seal_alt                        = Toba Regency Logo\n| motto                           = \"Tampakna do Rantosna, Rimni Tahi do Gogona\"\n| image_map                    